        "content": "<p>Hi folks. I'm picking <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"522295\">@Asahi Lina</span>'s xarray patches, and one of the invariants of XArray is that pointers stored in it must be 4-byte aligned. Ideally, I'd put that in a <code>where</code> clause, something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ForeignOwnable</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">where</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">FOREIGN_ALIGN</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but that syntax doesn't work of course. You can sorta fake it with <code>#![feature(generic_const_exprs)]</code> but I'm wondering: is there a better way? if not, is there an RFC that tracks the future existence of that better way?</p>",
        "id": 475928013,
        "sender_full_name": "Tamir Duberstein",
        "timestamp": 1728497400
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just keep it as a build_assert</p>",
        "id": 475930276,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728498304
    },
    {
